@jiripetrlik
Hi! All "equals" method of child classes have this snippet
  if (!super.equals(o)) { return false; }

so implementing "equals" on abstract/parent classes allow "equals" on children to also considering inherited fields.

@jiripetrlik
This is part of models that will be put in set/map/list - so having the equals/hashmap will avoid clashing of instances.
Beside that, IIRC it was suggested by Sonar. Last, I think it is a good practice to add such methods to DTOs because it add predictable behavior.

